sequenceDiagram
    participant CH as Cardholder
    participant POS as POS Terminal
    participant ACQ as Acquirer Processor
    participant NET as Card Network<br/>VisaNet or Banknet
    participant ISS as Issuing Bank

    Note over CH,ISS: PHASE 1 - AUTHORIZATION - Real-time, 1-3 seconds

    CH->>POS: Tap, insert, or swipe card
    POS->>POS: Read card data via EMV, NFC, or magstripe
    POS->>ACQ: ISO 8583 MTI 0100 Authorization Request
    ACQ->>ACQ: Validate merchant, append acquirer data
    ACQ->>NET: Route based on BIN prefix
    NET->>NET: Format validation, fraud scoring
    NET->>ISS: Forward authorization request
    ISS->>ISS: Check funds, fraud rules, velocity limits
    ISS-->>NET: Authorization Response - Approve or Decline
    NET-->>ACQ: Forward response with auth code
    ACQ-->>POS: Authorization response plus approval code
    POS-->>CH: Display Approved or Declined, print receipt

    Note over CH,ISS: PHASE 2 - CLEARING - Batch processing, end of day

    POS->>ACQ: Batch file of all transactions for the day
    ACQ->>NET: Submit clearing file - Visa TC05 or MC IPM
    NET->>NET: Match auths to clearing records, calculate interchange
    NET->>ISS: Deliver clearing records with interchange amounts

    Note over CH,ISS: PHASE 3 - SETTLEMENT - T+1 or T+2 business days

    ISS->>NET: Fund net settlement position
    NET->>NET: Calculate net positions across all members
    NET->>ACQ: Disburse net settlement amount
    ACQ->>POS: Fund merchant account minus MDR fees
    ISS->>CH: Post transaction to cardholder statement
